Follow all rules from this repository (adjust paths if you copy only the `.ai` folder elsewhere):

- `.ai/frontend.md` — Angular/SPA, `@rcubinity/core-angular`, API layer, models
- `.ai/backend.md` — NestJS-style HTTP services, shared in-repo `core/` layer, validation, routing contracts
- `.ai/python-services.md` — Python services, sockets, workers
- `.ai/context-and-docs.md` — colocated context docs, program-level atlas
- `.ai/devops.md` — containers, CI, config
- `.ai/security.md` — baseline security
- `.ai/testing.md` — tests and quality
- `.ai/review-checklist.md` — PR review

These rules are **generic** and **multi-project**. Repository-specific rules in each app’s `.cursor/rules/` or local docs **override** when they conflict.

Always aim for production-quality, maintainable code that matches the **existing** patterns in the target repository.
